summary: Healthcare solutions provider Solventum (NYSE:SOLV) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, but sales fell by 3.7% year on year to $2.00 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.36 per share was 37.3% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
